Description: Soothing Scents is a different kind of wellness company.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The Soothing Scents story goes all the way back to 2004, when nurse anesthetist Wendy Nichols began blending essential oils in her kitchen as an alternative way to help her patients deal with nausea after surgery. “It was distressing to see so many of my patients suffer from nausea and not be able to offer something that didn’t cause unwanted side effects, which many medications do,” says Nichols, who used her decades-long background in medicine to find a solution that was medically safe, and scientifically sound. What began as a homemade remedy quickly became a standard hospital supply, and finally, a growing business. Together with her brother, Roy Nichols, Wendy founded Soothing Scents: a small but big- hearted establishment that produces essential oil inhalers designed with the safety and science that healthcare environments demand. Today, our flagship blend QueaseEASE is used in over 1,000 hospitals and thousands of homes across America, by expectant mothers, boaters, nervous air travelers, road trip enthusiasts, deep sea divers, frequent flyers, chemotherapy patients, and those looking for a natural way to achieve mental focus and a better way to relax.

Full Description: S.T.A.R.S. Community Development Corporation is dedicated to uplifting disadvantaged communities in Las Vegas by disrupting at-risk lifestyles and helping individuals and families become empowered and successful. Its primary focus is mentoring youth to prevent teen pregnancy and ensure high school graduation. S.T.A.R.S. (Striving To Achieve Real Success) targets middle and high school students. Goal-Oriented and Family Engaged Youth Program Each student enters the program with specific written goals and S.T.A.R.S. creates benchmarks for six-week, six-month, one-year, and five-year time frames. Both the summer camp, Saturday, and the after-school mentoring program are designed to engage not only individual students but their families as well. This holistic approach results in deeper, more sustained emotional investment on the part of students, reinforcing the positive attitudes and behavior that lead to better academic performance and improved family and peer relationships. Involving their families amplifies the benefits because the more engaged parents are in their children’s academic and social development, the more effective outside mentoring and support can be. Involving the whole family can also help eliminate logistical barriers to participation.

Description: The Incite Agency is a communications solutions agency crafting integrated campaigns from start to finish.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The Incite Agency is a communications solutions agency crafting integrated campaigns from start to finish. The Incite Agency has worked with clients across the corporate spectrum, including Fortune 500 and other innovative companies in the technology, energy, education, health care and retail sectors in addition to a diverse range of advocacy and non-profit organizations.  The Incite Agency was founded in June 2013 by Ben Labolt and Robert Gibbs. Ben currently manages the agency. Ben advises Fortune 500 companies, cutting edge brands and prominent causes on how to transform communications efforts to be more proactive and agile, defend organizations under siege and tackle significant consumer and policy initiatives. In 2015, Ben was named to PR Week's 40 Under 40 list of industry leaders who "get results, never settle and represent the future of communications."  Co-Founder Robert is currently Executive Vice President and Global Chief Communications Officer at McDonald's Corporation. Robert has helped companies across a multitude of industries to create and implement communications strategies grounded in research and data and built for long-term success. A core member of the team that built the Obama brand from the ground up, beginning in 2004, when then-Senator Obama was a first-term legislator from Illinois, Robert previously served in several senior roles for President Obama, including White House Press Secretary—a role in which he developed communications strategies for the White House and served as the Obama administration’s primary voice on a wide range of complex issues. The New York Times called Robert the "president’s political compass".  Incite has a strategic partnership with Fenway Strategies to offer clients more services and hands-on support from a team that has worked at the highest levels of politics and for some of the most prominent Fortune 500 companies, cutting-edge start-ups, foundations, causes and campaigns. Fenway’s speechwriting and message development team works seamlessly with Incite’s crisis communications and digital team. Together, they are best equipped to help clients plan for and execute what we know best: fully integrated communications campaigns.

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: MyRentalUnits.com provides residential property owners and managers best practice advice, tools, information, forms, access to resources, reviews of products and services, as well as aggregration of content news, to enable them to more effectively and efficiently manager their rental housing property.    MRU provides quick and easy access to the superior website resources all property owners and managers need in their research library and electronic toolbox.  MRU searches the Internet for the business tools which make the property management business work better.  MRU reviews the sites and tools and lets members know which ones actually work or are worth the time.   MRU compiles the day's real estate news through RSS feeds and locates them in a single convenient location.  There is a MRU Forum where members can ask questions, discuss the hotest property management issues of the day and share advice.  And, when there is need for an expert to weigh in, the topic Moderator can help lead the group when appropriate or necessary.  MRU also gathers essential information for registered users. MRU finds the things that are important to the business of residential property management that most business owners do not have the time to locate.  Looking for a job in property management?  Visit the MRU Jobs Center and search our state-wide job listings.  Looking to hire?  Visit the MRU Jobs Center and post your available position.  MRU also has a free open access calendar where real estate events and meetings can be posted and shared. MRU is the vision of rental housing expert Merrie Turner Lightner, who after more than 20 years of property ownership and management saw the need for providing best practice information and advice to the housing providor of 1 to 20 units.   Currently these features and more are provided at no cost to registered users.  In 2009 with the formal launch of the site, a new membership tier will be offered at which time additional features will be made available to paid users and some of the previously free content will only be available to paid membership subscription users.
